Jimi Agbaje has been declared the winner of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) Lagos governorship primary for the 2019 general election. Agbaje, who was the party’s candidate in the 2015 election, contested for the ticket with Adedeji Doherty. He clinched the ticket again after an indirect election held on Thursday. He will be facing the ruling All Progressives Congress candidate, Babajide Sanwo-Olu, next February. Agbaje first contested for Lagos State governor in 2007 as the candidate of the Democratic People’s Alliance. He lost that election to Babatunde Fashola of the Action Congress. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .